## 850 Lab — Project Context for AI Assistants

### Architecture
- **Frontend**: React + Vite (in `web/`), served by FastAPI at port 5000
- **Backend**: FastAPI (`api/workflow_app.py`), PostgreSQL database (`database.py`)
- **Deployment**: Replit autoscale, FastAPI port 5000 serves built React SPA at `/` with SPA fallback + all `/api/*` routes
- **Build**: `pip install -r requirements.txt && cd web && npm install --production=false && npm run build`
- **Run**: `python -m uvicorn api.workflow_app:app --host 0.0.0.0 --port 5000`

### Key Files
- `api/workflow_app.py` — FastAPI app, all endpoints, startup lifespan with one-time data fixes
- `database.py` — PostgreSQL persistence layer, all table DDL, CRUD functions
- `services/customer_mail_service.py` — Certified mail sending via Lob, mail status builder, admin approval gate
- `services/customer_proof_service.py` — Proof document upload/management
- `letter_generator.py` — Dispute letter generation from parsed credit report data
- `lob_client.py` — Lob API integration for certified mail
- `web/src/` — React frontend

### Secrets (set in Replit, available as env vars)
- `DATABASE_URL` — PostgreSQL connection
- `WORKFLOW_ADMIN_API_SECRET` — Protects all `/internal/admin/...` endpoints (header: `X-Workflow-Admin-Key`)
- `LOB_API_KEY` — Lob certified mail API (live key)
- `AI_INTEGRATIONS_OPENAI_API_KEY` + `AI_INTEGRATIONS_OPENAI_BASE_URL` — OpenAI via Replit proxy

### Admin Endpoints (all require `X-Workflow-Admin-Key` header)
- `POST /internal/admin/mail/approve` — `{"user_id": N}` — approve customer for mailing
- `POST /internal/admin/mail/revoke` — `{"user_id": N}` — revoke mail approval
- `GET /internal/admin/mail/approval-status/{user_id}` — check approval
- `POST /internal/admin/proof/reassign-orphaned` — reassign proof uploads
- `POST /internal/admin/entitlements/grant` — grant credits
- `POST /internal/admin/responses/override-classification` — override response classification
- `POST /internal/admin/responses/override-escalation` — override escalation recommendation

### Mail Approval Gate
Every customer must be admin-approved before they can send certified mail. The `mail_approvals` table tracks approvals. The check happens in `send_certified_letter_for_bureau()` and the status appears in `_build_mail_status()`. Admins bypass this check.

